      <description>Yes, multiple tools can detect 502 Bad Gateway errors by monitoring server responses, checking uptime, and alerting you instantly. These include cloud-based monitors like Pingdom, open-source solutions like Uptime Kuma, and browser extensions. They help you quickly identify and fix upstream server issues, minimizing downtime.</description>
